            . I am a builder. I live in <placeName id="t18130217-91-crimeloc540">Brunswick-square, in the parish of St. Pancras</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18130217-91-crimeloc540" type="placeName" value="Brunswick-square, in the parish of St. Pancras"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18130217-91-crimeloc540" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18130217-91-off537 t18130217-91-crimeloc540"></join>. On Sunday, the 7th of February, I was in my dwelling-house, looking out of the window; I could see over the fields where he Company of the West Middlesex water-works have pipes lay there. I saw some person busy at something. I went out of my house. The prisoner was standing with a sledge hammer in the attitude of striking the pipe, and a quantity of pieces broken off the pipe were laying by the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Q. He was in the act of breaking these pipes - A. Yes, he was.</p>
               <p>Q. You did not wait to see whether he carried them, away did you - A. No.</p>
